dismissalComment.html: length delivery outside the off stump and Siddique drives on the up but there is no timing, goes in the air to Matsikenyeri at cover, who gobbles up an easy catch.

Chigumbura picks up a second, Tamim looking to drive through the off side, the ball moves away and with it takes the edge to Taibu behind the wicket to his left. Bangladesh in a spot of bother at 5 for 2.

headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Ashraful falls, looking for the big booming drive through the off side, there was width and he edges it through to Taibu, Chigumbura is excited, picks up his third wicket.

Shakib too departs! good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing there. Shakib drives well away from his body and ends up with a faint edge -  was a nothing shot and Taibu does the rest. Bangladesh 5 down and in deep trouble here.

That's the end of that! Bangladesh in total disarray here! back of a length and close to the off stump line, came in with the angle. Mahmudullah looks to work it away on the leg side but fails miserably and the edge goes straight to Price at first slip. Four more to go

dismissalComment.html: dead plumb in front. It was the armer, drifting in the on the middle stump line, Chibhaba, who was struggling against spin, leaned forward to defend but pushed outside the line, perhaps expecting the ball to turn away. Mistake. The ball hit him right in front of the middle. Gone!

Another easy decision to make for Nadir Shah. Another arm ball. It landed just outside off stump and moved in. Taylor moved forward rather hesitantly unsure whether its going to turn away or come in. The ball moved in past the poke and hit him in front. It would have hit leg and middle or at least the leg stump.

image.caption: Tatenda Taibu
image.longCaption: Tatenda Taibu portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalComment.html: What is going on out there?! Comical stuff from Taibu. Again he shapes to sweep way ahead before the delivery is bowled; the ball drops short and turns away from the off stump. Taibu, already on a bent knee, tries to adjust and tries to swat it to the on side but only drags it back to his stumps. Three wickets in this over. Zimbabwe struggling here after quite a decent start

headshotImage.caption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Important breakthrough achieved. It was the short delivery outside off, Coventry tried to fetch it from there as he went for the pull but didn't connect well and it lobbed up. Razzak ran in from deep midwicket and caught it on the rebound.

commentTextItems.html: Crash. Bang. Short and wide, slapped away hard to the cover boundary. Zimbabwe win by 5 wickets. The Bangladesh players shake hands with the batsmen. What a wonderful partnership between the two to take Zim home with 15 overs to spare.

commentPostTextItems.html: Please hang on for quotes from post-match ceremony.

Shakib: "I thought we didn't bat properly and we didn't execute our plans well. We lost too many wickets early and that lost us the game. Dollar and Rahim played well. There are four more games and I am sure we can come back."
Masakadza (Utseya injured): "It's a great start to the series. Chasing was always better. That partnership between took us home and Chigumbura bowled well also."

Chigumbura is the Man of the Match: "I set the tone with the bowling and finished off the game with the bat. You needed to bowl in the right areas, that's when you create chances. I just knew that we had to get a big partnership and it came on."
That's it from us. Join us for the second ODI. Till then its good bye and good luck.

commentTextItems.html: goes right back to defend to the on side
shorter in length, quicker one, skids on straight, pulled to left of mid-on
loopy delivery around off and middle, gets the edge but goes wide of slip
stays back to a length delivery and squeezes it wide of backward point for a single
tosses this up and pushed down to long-off without any fuss
leans forward to drive it back to the bowler
What a stylish way to reach the fifty. It was short in length and Chigumbura, the star today, pulled it high over midwicket boundary. 12th ODI fifty.
on the middle, worked wide of mid-on
flighted on the off stump line, eased down to long-off
length delivery in the zone outside off stump, tries to dab it to third man but is beaten

commentPreTextItems.html: Play held up again. Do we have yet another crowd trouble. Ash went up to the square-leg umpire and had a chat. Not sure whats happening out there. The umpires call the ground authorities. The vice president of the Bangladesh cricket board walks out to discuss things with the umpires.

commentTextItems.html: on the leg stump line, again tapped towards mid-on and they take the run
Wallop. Chigumbura is having a blast out there. Full pitched just outside off and he thrashed it wide of mid-off for yet another boundary
short delivery outside off, goes for the upper cut but doesn't connect.
goes for the yorker, falls short of the block hole, around 131 kmph, Matsikenyeri drives it straight past the bowler
length delivery around the off stump line, pushed to mid-off and they take a easy run! The fielding has been pretty poor actually ...
on the off and middle, pushed away to point

dismissalComment.html: length delivery outside the off stump and Siddique drives on the up but there is no timing, goes in the air to Matsikenyeri at cover, who gobbles up an easy catch.

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal c †Taibu b Chigumbura 5 (11b 1x4 0x6 17m) SR: 45.45

dismissalComment.html: Chigumbura picks up a second, Tamim looking to drive through the off side, the ball moves away and with it takes the edge to Taibu behind the wicket to his left. Bangladesh in a spot of bother at 5 for 2.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Ashraful c †Taibu b Chigumbura 20 (41b 2x4 1x6 59m) SR: 48.78

dismissalComment.html: Ashraful falls, looking for the big booming drive through the off side, there was width and he edges it through to Taibu, Chigumbura is excited, picks up his third wicket.

dismissalText.commentary: Raqibul Hasan run out (Chigumbura/†Taibu) 16 (44b 1x4 0x6 68m) SR: 36.36

dismissalComment.html: suicide! tossed up delivery, Raqibul works it away behind square on the leg side and calls for the single, Shakib takes a couple of steps and then changes his mind but its too late for Raqibul as Chigumbura's throw comes in at the striker's end and Taibu clips the bails with Raqibul out by a long way

image.caption: Tatenda Taibu
image.longCaption: Tatenda Taibu portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c †Taibu b Chibhabha 13 (16b 2x4 0x6 21m) SR: 81.25

dismissalComment.html: Shakib too departs! good length delivery outside the off stump, hint of away swing there. Shakib drives well away from his body and ends up with a faint edge -  was a nothing shot and Taibu does the rest. Bangladesh 5 down and in deep trouble here.

image.caption: Ray Price
image.longCaption: Ray Price portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Mahmudullah c Price b Chibhabha 4 (2b 1x4 0x6 2m) SR: 200

dismissalComment.html: That's the end of that! Bangladesh in total disarray here! back of a length and close to the off stump line, came in with the angle. Mahmudullah looks to work it away on the leg side but fails miserably and the edge goes straight to Price at first slip. Four more to go

dismissalText.long: c Raqibul Hasan b Rubel Hossain
dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza c Raqibul Hasan b Rubel Hossain 10 (31b 1x4 0x6 56m) SR: 32.25

dismissalComment.html: Four down and a stunner to remove Masakadza. It was short and slightly wide, Masakadza gave it the full treatment and it flew to the left of backward point where Raqibul pulled of a very fine reflex catch. Masakadza looks stunned and he should be. That was a sharp catch

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha lbw b Abdur Razzak 26 (28b 3x4 1x6 31m) SR: 92.85

dismissalComment.html: dead plumb in front. It was the armer, drifting in the on the middle stump line, Chibhaba, who was struggling against spin, leaned forward to defend but pushed outside the line, perhaps expecting the ball to turn away. Mistake. The ball hit him right in front of the middle. Gone!

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor lbw b Abdur Razzak 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Another easy decision to make for Nadir Shah. Another arm ball. It landed just outside off stump and moved in. Taylor moved forward rather hesitantly unsure whether its going to turn away or come in. The ball moved in past the poke and hit him in front. It would have hit leg and middle or at least the leg stump.

headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu b Abdur Razzak 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: What is going on out there?! Comical stuff from Taibu. Again he shapes to sweep way ahead before the delivery is bowled; the ball drops short and turns away from the off stump. Taibu, already on a bent knee, tries to adjust and tries to swat it to the on side but only drags it back to his stumps. Three wickets in this over. Zimbabwe struggling here after quite a decent start
